tags

	C-] -> adds tag to tagstack, go to it
	:[N]po[p] -> jump down the tag stack 
	:[N]ta[g] -> go up the tag stack
	:tags -> list tag stack
	:tag NAME -> goes into tag with name
	:ptag NAME -> opens tag in prev. window
	:ts /pattern -> lists tags to get to
	:tag /pattern -> go to tag with pattern
		-> if there are multiple, use
		tn, tp to jump between
	au BufEnter * :tag / 

	nnoremap <C-[> :pop<CR>
	-- what to map :tag to?

	nnoremap [t :tag<cr>
	nnoremap ]t :pop<cr>


	-> calling C-] will clean the tag stack
	   from the point where we are in it

	Is it possible to highlight all the tags in the current file?
	Yes. Read the Vim online help on "tag-highlight". 

